      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ : «أَ لاَ أُنَبِّئُكُمْ بِشَرِّ اَلنَّاسِ » قَالُوا بَلَى يَا رَسُولَ اَللَّهِ قَالَ «مَنْ سَافَرَ وَحْدَهُ وَ مَنَعَ رِفْدَهُ وَ ضَرَبَ عَبْدَهُ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2432 - Ali ibn Asbat narrated from Abdul-Malik ibn Maslamah, from al-Sarri ibn Khalid, from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\nThe Messenger of Allah (swt) (peace and blessings of Allah (swt) be upon him and his family) said:\n\"Shall I inform you of the worst of people?\"\nThey said: \"Yes, O Messenger of Allah (swt).\"\nHe (sw) said: \"The one who travels alone, denies giving aid, and strikes their servant.\""
        ]
      }
    },
